    "Here we propose using circular obstacles to form a simple chiral lattice to separate CW and CCW particles.",
    "Specifically, we consider a mirror-symmetry broken parallelogram lattice (Fig. 9a-d), which can be created by horizontally shifting each layer of a square lattice by a constant distance δd, where d is the lattice constant and δ is the shape parameter with δ ∈ [0, 1) (Fig.",
    "The packing fraction ϕ of the lattice will be invariant during this operation.",
    "The deformed lattice preserves the mirror symmetry at δ = 0, 0.5 and 1 (Fig. 9e).",
    "For other values of δ, the lattice has a broken mirror symmetry as its unit cell cannot overlap with its mirror image."
